<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-WWKFty63klICoiR5ixGCUA" name=",_GUcF0MhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" guid="-WWKFty63klICoiR5ixGCUA" changeDate="2008-12-12T12:29:24.573+0100">
  <sections xmi:id="_LeFgMMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Identify most important requirements for each functional slice and how to evaluate them " guid="_LeFgMMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>For each functional slice (corresponding to abstract services descriptions) define which the most important requirements are, using the Service Composition Specification as input. Those requirements will be used to determine which the best option to implement the functionality is. The objective is to weigh the importance of each requirement. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Metrics and evaluation methods can be defined to analyse possible candidates. The data collected will be used to establish requirements matching score. Moreover, if a service offers more features, it could receive extra points for making easier a possible evolution or improvement of the composition. Point out which extra features could give higher score to a service. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_MdRsUMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Do the mapping between services and functional slices " guid="_MdRsUMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Next step is to analyse each service specification to ascertain the abstract functionalities that the service can carry out. This implies relating real service implementation with abstract services descriptions. It is possible that the same service is used for various functionalities. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>If the list of candidates was categorized, this mapping will be easier. Another suggestion to do the mapping is to use previous ERA, to reuse other solutions which were useful in the past. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Have in mind those requirements deducted from the composition design which facilitate the integration and collaboration between services&lt;/SPAN></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_N1y-cMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Evaluate each service to know the level of matching with requirements " guid="_N1y-cMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Using the evaluation method obtained in the first step, calculate the score of each service implementation. In the case that the same service maps with more than one functional slice, calculate the score for each functionality. Do not forget to evaluate the extra points if the composition is expected to be evolved later. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_PXHAMMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw" name="Analyse which parts of the composition have not been mapped with services " guid="_PXHAMMhAEd2n-93vLaUXdw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Finally, detect which parts of the functionality of the composition are not covered and mark them as functionalities to be developed. It can be developed in the company or contracted to a third party. In the case there is no possibility to obtain it; the composition should be modified due to the fact that it cannot be implemented. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Note for companies which develop services: These gaps in the composition could be opportunities for the company to develop new services. It could be more profitable to develop the service than to relax the requirements. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>In&#xD;
this task, the purpose is to relate abstract descriptions included in the composition design with services specifications&#xD;
selected as candidates for the implementation of the composition.&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
